<title>LATVIA: BALTIC SHARE MARKET BEING FORMED, OFFICIAL SAYS.</title>
<headline>BALTIC SHARE MARKET BEING FORMED, OFFICIAL SAYS.</headline>
<dateline>RIGA 1997-03-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>The basis for a pan-Baltic equities market have already been formed with signing of an agreement between the Estonian and Latvian depositories, an official of the planned Latvian securities market commission said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>&quot;The basis for a pan-Baltic equities market is already there,&quot; Talis Laizans, future deputy chairman of the commission told Reuters in an interview.</p>
<p>Laizans said the Riga stock exchange should invest more in technology in order to maintain its central role, Laizans said.</p>
<p>&quot;Much more (investment) is needed in order to remain competitive in a year, two years time,&quot; he said.</p>
<p>-- Martinsh Gravitis, Riga Newsroom,+371 721 5240</p>
